      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">An anxious mother consults about her 2-year-old child, who exhibits delayed developmental milestones, signs of intellectual disability, and sandal gap toes. The child, recently diagnosed with a heart condition, is also identified to have a trisomy disorder. Accompanying this information is an image depicting the child&#39;s eye findings characteristic of the trisomy disorder. Given this clinical background, what is the most common cause of intestinal obstruction in this child?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/27/picture14_E9y44hu.jpg\" style=\"height:275px; width:300px\" /></span></span></span></p>",
