      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">During a routine pediatric visit, an 8-month-old girl named Saheli is brought in by her mother, who is concerned about her daughter&#39;s chronic diarrhea lasting over a month and failure to thrive. Saheli presents with abdominal distension and facial pallor, and a routine complete blood count (CBC) reveals severe anemia. The mother reports that these symptoms began after weaning Saheli off breast milk and introducing supplementary feeds. Further evaluation indicates Saheli has a hypersensitivity to gliadin in her diet. Given this clinical picture, which specific antibody is most likely to be present in Saheli? </span></span></span></p>",
