        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">An anxious mother presents her 10-year-old child to the clinic, concerned about a lesion in his mouth, shown in an accompanying image. The child&#39;s uncle was recently diagnosed with a gastrointestinal malignancy, heightening her concern about her son&#39;s risk for developing cancer. Upon examination, you note the oral lesion and identify a hamartomatous polyp. Given these clinical findings, what is the most likely diagnosis, and which gene is implicated?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2024/03/27/picture16_eYi22rC.jpg\" style=\"height:206px; width:300px\" /></span></span></span></p>",
